OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1774624292
OL,3,CPolice admit 'terrible error' telling
OL,4,Cpartner of Ian Coates how he died
OL,6,FA detective chief inspector at
OL,7,FNottinghamshire Police has told a
OL,8,Fpublic inquiry that telling the
OL,9,Fpartner of a man who was stabbed to
OL,10,Fdeath by Valdo Calocane that he had
OL,11,Fdied in a road traffic collision was a
OL,12,F"terrible error".
OL,14,FElaine Newton told the hearing on
OL,15,FTuesday it felt like her partner Ian
OL,16,FCoates, 65, had been killed twice
OL,17,Fbecause she was first told he had died
OL,18,Fin a car crash before being informed
OL,19,Fmore than four hours later he had
OL,20,Factually been stabbed by Valdo
OL,21,FCalocane.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@PO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/10
